  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to restore my lost Yahoo toolbar?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Yahoo toolbar, here are the steps you can take to restore it:\n\n### For Browsers Like Chrome or Firefox:\n\n1. **Check Toolbar Visibility:**\n   - Right-click on the top area of your browser (or look for the menu in some browsers) and see if there's an option to show/hide the toolbar. Make sure it is checked or enabled.\n\n2. **Reinstall the Yahoo Toolbar:**\n   - Visit the official Yahoo Toolbar download page or search for \"Yahoo Toolbar download\" in a search engine.\n   - Follow the instructions to download and install it again.\n   - After installation, restart your browser and check if the toolbar appears.\n\n3. **Browser Reset:**\n   - If the toolbar is still missing, you might want to consider resetting your browser. This will restore default settings and may bring back the toolbar.\n   - **Chrome:** Go to Settings > Advanced > Reset settings.\n   - **Firefox:** Go to Help > Troubleshooting Information > Refresh Firefox.\n\n### For Internet Explorer (if applicable):\n\n1. **Manage Add-ons:**\n   - Open Internet Explorer, and click on the gear icon (Tools), then select **Manage add-ons**.\n   - Look for Yahoo Toolbar under Toolbars and Extensions, and make sure it is enabled.\n\n2. **Reinstall the Yahoo Toolbar:**\n   - If the toolbar is not listed or is disabled, download the Yahoo Toolbar again from the Yahoo website.\n\n3. **Check the View Menu:**\n   - Go to the View menu, then select **Toolbars** and see if Yahoo Toolbar is checked.\n\n### General Tips:\n\n- **Browser Extensions:** Ensure that the Yahoo toolbar extension is not disabled in your browser\u2019s extensions or add-on section.\n- **Clear Cache and Cookies:** Sometimes clearing your browser's cache and cookies can solve visibility issues.\n- **Antivirus/Firewall Settings:** Some security software may block toolbars. Check your antivirus or firewall settings.\n\n### Note:\nSince Yahoo discontinued its toolbar service for many users, if you cannot find the Yahoo Toolbar via typical installation methods, you may need to consider using an alternative browser feature or a different tool that replicates the functionality you need.\n\nIf you're referring to Yahoo's newer services or tools, consider checking Yahoo's website or help center for the latest updates and tools available.",
